<section id="about" class="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">Origin</p>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>The Car That<br /><em>Chapman Built</em></h2>
        <p>
          Colin Chapman had one governing philosophy: remove everything that isn't essential.
          The Super 7 was his purest application of that idea — a road car stripped to the
          barest mechanical truth, where aluminium panels are stretched over a thin
          spaceframe and nothing separates driver from road.
        </p>
        <p>
          Introduced in 1957 and refined into the Series II by 1960, the Super 7 arrived at
          a moment when British sports cars were still hand-built curiosities. The Series II
          brought cleaner lines, a cycle-winged body, and compatibility with the new Ford
          105E overhead-valve engine — a step change in refinement over the outgoing
          side-valve unit.
        </p>
        <p>
          By 1962 the Super 7 had matured into something rare: a car that was simultaneously
          a practical road machine and a genuine club racer. You bought it as a kit, paid less
          purchase tax, and assembled it yourself. The labour was part of the ownership.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="about-aside">
        <dl class="provenance">
          <div>
            <dt>Chassis series</dt>
            <dd>Series II</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Production years</dt>
            <dd>1960 – 1968</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Country</dt>
            <dd>United Kingdom</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Manufacturer</dt>
            <dd>Lotus Cars, Cheshunt</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Build type</dt>
            <dd>Factory kit (customer-assembled)</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Body style</dt>
            <dd>Open two-seat roadster</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about {
    background: var(--bg-section);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  h2 em {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-text p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .about-text p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-aside {
    align-self: start;
  }

  .provenance {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .provenance div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .provenance div:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .provenance dt {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .provenance dd {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
